  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ Gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> and 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4] </span><strong>carrots </strong>(no need to peel!) into rough bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes </strong>and<strong> carrots</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 10-12 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once done, drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1623678510951-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1623678510951-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1623678510951-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1623678510951-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1623678510951-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are cooking, reboil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Top, tail, and dice the<strong> remaining carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1623678516573-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1623678516573-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1623678516573-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1623678516573-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1623678516573-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong>, <strong>carrot </strong>and<strong> garlic </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve the<strong> chicken stock mix</strong> and<strong> tomato paste</strong> in 250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> and add the <strong>Henderson's relish</strong> and <strong>dried basil</strong> – this is your<strong> tomato stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1623678522127-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1623678522127-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1623678522127-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1623678522127-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1623678522127-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the vegetables have softened, add the <strong>turkey mince </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until browned, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Grate the <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Once the turkey is browned, add the <strong>tomato stock </strong>to the pan and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Season with a grind of<strong> black pepper</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until slightly thickened – this is your <strong>turkey mixture</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1623678530066-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
